"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-news-world-europe-paris-olympics-seine-protest-b2560483.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Organisers have vowed to conduct a 's*** flashmob' as President Macron takes to the water  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 412, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 270, \"end\": 286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"President Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  France'srevolutionary spirit is being re-lit by theOlympicflame as it has emerged Parisians are planning an outrageous manner of protest ahead of thegames this summer.\", \"from\": 413, \"to\": 604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Renowned for theircreative demonstrations, the French could out-do themselves as angry residents protest their government's spending on the world's stage.\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9989396553007504, \"rank\": 0.0009979988798245532, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Parisians have expressed their discontent for the event as they say much-needed funds are being wasted on the games while neighbourhoods in the city struggle with poverty.\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the biggest controversies is the French government's plan tohost events in the River Seineitself - despite the dirty water having been un-swimmable for a century.\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 1104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 975, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9989396553007504, \"rank\": 0.0009979988798245532, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Authorities have allocated \\u00a31.2 billion to the state-backed plan to\\u00a0clean up the Seine ahead of the world's top athletes taking a dip.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1187, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999997266968, \"rank\": 1.712334981723316e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the water still being too dirty to swim in just weeks away from the event, President Emmanuel has vowed to swim in the river himself on June 23 to prove the initiative's success.\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1335, \"end\": 1343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"score\": 0.9999999983992893, \"rank\": 1.227658276949683e-09, \"text\": \"Emmanuel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When asked if he would swim in the Seine, Macron told reporters: \\\"You bet I will.\\\"\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1465, \"end\": 1470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999997266968, \"rank\": 1.712334981723316e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1472, \"end\": 1478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.702337882793538e-18, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In response, creative frenchmen have devised a plan to soil their leaders' plan - literally.\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Parisians have vowed to fill the river with human faeces on the day Emmanuel and the French mayor Anne Hidalgo take to the water in what they dubbed a \\\"s*** flashmob\\\".\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1676, \"end\": 1684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"score\": 0.9999999983992893, \"rank\": 1.227658276949683e-09, \"text\": \"Emmanuel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\"}, {\"begin\": 1693, \"end\": 1699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9989396553007504, \"rank\": 0.0009979988798245532, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1706, \"end\": 1718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hashtag\\u00a0#JeChieDansLaSeineLe23Juin, which translates to \\\"I s*** in the Seine on June 23\\\" began trending at the end of last month and has since gained traction across social media.\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1852, \"end\": 1857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999997266968, \"rank\": 1.712334981723316e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The initial post on X has gained over half a million impressions and posts on TikTok spreading the word have garnered well over a million views.\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 2106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2040, \"end\": 2046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.820559661181692e-36, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As news of the protest, memes such as AI generated pictures of toilets along the Seine and Macron standing on a bridge covered in faeces sprung up across French X.\", \"from\": 2108, \"to\": 2271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2146, \"end\": 2148, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999956353162571, \"rank\": 4.364702518542718e-06, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 2189, \"end\": 2194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999997266968, \"rank\": 1.712334981723316e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2199, \"end\": 2205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.702337882793538e-18, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Upon the hashtag gaining traction, website dedicated to the campaign has cropped up with a handy tool to inform people exactly what time they should empty their bowels into the river based on their distance away from Paris.\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2490, \"end\": 2495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997926352, \"rank\": 2.0746578273299477e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The message on the websites homepage reads: \\\"Because after putting us in s*** it is up to them to bathe in our s***\\\"  Olympic Open water and triathlon events are scheduled to take place in the river during the games from26 July to 11 Augustas the city receives a facelift to accommodate more than 10,500 athletes from around the world.\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2833, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have made clear that there is no Plan B if the water quality does not meet European safety standards during the two weeks of the games.\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 2981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming in the river been barred on safety grounds since 1923 - a year before the city last hosted the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2983, \"to\": 3101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Concerns that the races will have to be postponed are growing each day as the river continues to fail water quality tests and after heavy rainfall in May.\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3257, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One reading for E.Coli near the triathlon start line was more than three times the required level.\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3356, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The river is just one point of contention as the city gears up to host the event.\", \"from\": 3358, \"to\": 3439, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week it was revealed thatParisauthorities have removed thousands of homeless people from the streetsahead of the Olympic Gamesin what campaignershave called a \\\"clean-up\\\" driveof those \\\"considered undesirable\\\".\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paul Alauzy, of health monitoring charity M\\u00e9decins du Monde, described it as \\\"social cleansing\\\" of the most vulnerable people in efforts to \\\"appear in the most flattering light possible\\\" for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3861, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3863, \"to\": 4093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3914, \"end\": 3925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2832944382506823e-16, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"